Today’s vote is a victory for Dreamers as well as TPS and DED recipients, but we will not stop here. We will continue to fight for true, comprehensive immigration reform that honors our heritage as a proud nation of immigrants, upholds our laws, and reflects our values.
We now implore the Senate to follow suit and do what is right for our country. It would then be up to President Trump to decide if he wants to remain on the wrong side of history.

The American Dream and Promise Act, #HR6, resolves part of the problem, securing protections for U.S. residents living under these designations and giving them and their families certainty and peace of mind.
Our @HispanicCaucus has worked tirelessly, meeting weekly while in Washington, in search of solutions to an immigration system that is not working.

I was proud to cast my vote today to protect Dreamers, Temporary Protected Status holders, and those covered by Deferred Enforced Departure and to provide these individuals with a pathway to citizenship and an opportunity to fulfill the promise of the American Dream.

As a proud nation of immigrants from around the world, the American Dream and Promise Act honors our history & our heritage. Looking forward to #HR6 passing the House today! pic.twitter.com/0ds31vAi38
